{{!--
  Premium Private Residential Tenancy (PRT) Agreement
  Scotland - Professional Edition

  This template generates a beautifully formatted, legally comprehensive
  Private Residential Tenancy agreement compliant with the Private Housing
  (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.
--}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-GB">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Premium Private Residential Tenancy Agreement - Scotland</title>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 20mm 15mm;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .document-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      padding: 30px 0;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #1e5a8e;
    }

    .document-title {
      font-size: 28pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      margin: 0 0 10px 0;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    .document-subtitle {
      font-size: 14pt;
      color: #4a5568;
      margin: 5px 0;
    }

    .scotland-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e5a8e 0%, #2d3748 100%);
      color: white;
      padding: 8px 20px;
      border-radius: 20px;
      font-size: 10pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 15px;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .agreement-date {
      font-size: 12pt;
      color: #718096;
      margin-top: 15px;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .section-header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e5a8e 0%, #2d3748 100%);
      color: white;
      padding: 15px 20px;
      margin: 40px 0 20px 0;
      font-size: 16pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
      page-break-after: avoid;
    }

    .section-number {
      background: white;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      border-radius: 50%;
      width: 35px;
      height: 35px;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      margin-right: 15px;
      font-size: 16pt;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .subsection {
      margin: 25px 0;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .subsection-title {
      font-size: 13pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      border-left: 4px solid #1e5a8e;
      padding-left: 15px;
    }

    .clause {
      margin: 15px 0;
      padding-left: 30px;
    }

    .clause-number {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      display: inline-block;
      min-width: 40px;
    }

    .explainer-box {
      background: #f7fafc;
      border-left: 4px solid #4299e1;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 15px 0;
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: #4a5568;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .explainer-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .explainer-icon {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-right: 8px;
      font-size: 14pt;
    }

    .scotland-legal-box {
      background: #f0f9ff;
      border: 2px solid #1e5a8e;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 15px 0;
      font-size: 10pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .scotland-legal-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 11pt;
    }

    .warning-box {
      background: #fff5f5;
      border-left: 4px solid #f56565;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 15px 0;
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: #742a2a;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .warning-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #c53030;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .important-box {
      background: #fffaf0;
      border: 2px solid #ed8936;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 15px 0;
      font-size: 10pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .important-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #c05621;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 11pt;
    }

    .party-details {
      background: #f7fafc;
      padding: 20px;
      margin: 15px 0;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid #cbd5e0;
    }

    .party-label {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      font-size: 12pt;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .party-info {
      margin-left: 20px;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .property-highlight {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e5a8e 0%, #2d3748 100%);
      color: white;
      padding: 25px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      border-radius: 8px;
      text-align: center;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .property-address {
      font-size: 18pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .property-details {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 15px;
      margin-top: 15px;
    }

    .property-detail-item {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      padding: 10px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .property-detail-label {
      font-size: 9pt;
      opacity: 0.8;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .property-detail-value {
      font-size: 12pt;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .financial-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 20px 0;
      background: white;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }

    .financial-table th {
      background: #1e5a8e;
      color: white;
      padding: 15px;
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 10pt;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .financial-table td {
      padding: 15px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    }

    .financial-table tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .financial-table .label {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #4a5568;
    }

    .financial-table .value {
      font-size: 13pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
    }

    .inventory-section {
      background: #f9fafb;
      padding: 20px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      border: 1px solid #cbd5e0;
      border-radius: 8px;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .inventory-title {
      font-size: 14pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .inventory-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 15px;
    }

    .inventory-item {
      background: white;
      padding: 10px;
      border-left: 3px solid #1e5a8e;
    }

    .signature-section {
      margin-top: 60px;
      page-break-before: always;
      padding-top: 40px;
    }

    .signature-title {
      font-size: 18pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    .signature-blocks {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 40px;
      margin: 40px 0;
    }

    .signature-block {
      border: 2px solid #1e5a8e;
      padding: 30px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: #f7fafc;
    }

    .signature-party {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1e5a8e;
      font-size: 12pt;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .signature-name {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .signature-line {
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1e5a8e;
      margin: 30px 0 10px 0;
      height: 50px;
    }

    .signature-label {
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #718096;
      margin-top: 5px;
    }

    .signature-date {
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .signature-date-label {
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #718096;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .signature-date-line {
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1e5a8e;
      width: 150px;
      height: 30px;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 10px 0;
      padding-left: 30px;
    }

    li {
      margin: 8px 0;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 40px;
      padding-top: 20px;
      border-top: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #718096;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- DOCUMENT HEADER -->
  <div class="document-header">
    <div class="document-title">Private Residential Tenancy Agreement</div>
    <div class="document-subtitle">Premium Professional Edition</div>
    <div class="scotland-badge">üè¥Û†ÅßÛ†Å¢Û†Å≥Û†Å£Û†Å¥Û†Åø SCOTLAND - Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016</div>
    <div class="agreement-date">Agreement Date: {{agreement_date}}</div>
  </div>

  <div class="scotland-legal-box">
    <div class="scotland-legal-title">üìã About This Agreement</div>
    <p>This is a <strong>Private Residential Tenancy (PRT)</strong> under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016. PRTs replaced Assured and Short Assured Tenancies for all new private tenancies in Scotland from 1 December 2017.</p>
    <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>‚úì No fixed end date (open-ended tenancy)</li>
      <li>‚úì Enhanced tenant protections</li>
      <li>‚úì Rent increase restrictions (12-month minimum gap)</li>
      <li>‚úì Mandatory landlord registration</li>
      <li>‚úì Deposit protection within 30 working days</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 1: PARTIES -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">1</span>
    THE PARTIES TO THIS AGREEMENT
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">1.1 The Landlord</div>
    <div class="party-details">
      <div class="party-label">LANDLORD DETAILS</div>
      <div class="party-info">
        <strong>Name:</strong> {{landlord_full_name}}<br>
        {{#if landlord_2_name}}
        <strong>Joint Landlord:</strong> {{landlord_2_name}}<br>
        {{/if}}
        <strong>Address:</strong> {{landlord_address}}<br>
        <strong>Email:</strong> {{landlord_email}}<br>
        <strong>Phone:</strong> {{landlord_phone}}
        {{#if landlord_reg_number}}
        <br><strong>Registration Number:</strong> {{landlord_reg_number}}
        <br><strong>Registration Authority:</strong> {{registration_authority}}
        {{#if registration_expiry}}
        <br><strong>Registration Expiry:</strong> {{registration_expiry}}
        {{/if}}
        {{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if landlord_reg_number}}
    <div class="explainer-box">
      <div class="explainer-title">
        <span class="explainer-icon">‚úì</span>
        Landlord Registration Confirmed
      </div>
      <p>The landlord is registered with {{registration_authority}} as required by the Antisocial Behaviour etc. (Scotland) Act 2004. It is a criminal offence to let property in Scotland without being a registered landlord.</p>
    </div>
    {{else}}
    <div class="warning-box">
      <div class="warning-title">‚ö†Ô∏è Landlord Registration Required</div>
      <p><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> The landlord MUST be registered with the local authority before this tenancy can commence. Letting property without registration is a criminal offence carrying fines up to ¬£50,000.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  {{#if agent_name}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">1.2 The Letting Agent</div>
    <div class="party-details">
      <div class="party-label">AGENT DETAILS</div>
      <div class="party-info">
        <strong>Name:</strong> {{agent_name}}<br>
        <strong>Address:</strong> {{agent_address}}<br>
        <strong>Email:</strong> {{agent_email}}<br>
        <strong>Phone:</strong> {{agent_phone}}
        {{#if agent_reg_number}}
        <br><strong>Agent Registration Number:</strong> {{agent_reg_number}}
        {{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">1.3 The Tenant(s)</div>
    {{#each tenants}}
    <div class="party-details">
      <div class="party-label">TENANT {{number}}</div>
      <div class="party-info">
        <strong>Name:</strong> {{full_name}}<br>
        <strong>Date of Birth:</strong> {{dob}}<br>
        <strong>Email:</strong> {{email}}<br>
        <strong>Phone:</strong> {{phone}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/each}}

    {{#if multiple_tenants}}
    <div class="explainer-box">
      <div class="explainer-title">
        <span class="explainer-icon">‚ÑπÔ∏è</span>
        Joint and Several Liability
      </div>
      <p>All tenants are jointly and severally liable for the rent and all obligations under this agreement. This means each tenant is individually responsible for the full rent amount and all terms, not just their share.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 2: PROPERTY -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">2</span>
    THE PROPERTY
  </div>

  <div class="property-highlight">
    <div class="property-address">{{property_address}}</div>
    <div class="property-details">
      {{#if property_type}}
      <div class="property-detail-item">
        <div class="property-detail-label">Property Type</div>
        <div class="property-detail-value">{{property_type}}</div>
      </div>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_bedrooms}}
      <div class="property-detail-item">
        <div class="property-detail-label">Bedrooms</div>
        <div class="property-detail-value">{{number_of_bedrooms}}</div>
      </div>
      {{/if}}
      <div class="property-detail-item">
        <div class="property-detail-label">Furnished Status</div>
        <div class="property-detail-value">{{furnished_status}}</div>
      </div>
      {{#if council_tax_band}}
      <div class="property-detail-item">
        <div class="property-detail-label">Council Tax Band</div>
        <div class="property-detail-value">Band {{council_tax_band}}</div>
      </div>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </div>

  {{#if property_description}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">2.1 Property Description</div>
    <p>{{property_description}}</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if included_areas}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">2.2 Included Areas</div>
    <p>The following areas are included in the let property:</p>
    <p>{{included_areas}}</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if excluded_areas}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">2.3 Excluded Areas</div>
    <div class="warning-box">
      <div class="warning-title">Areas NOT Included</div>
      <p>{{excluded_areas}}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if parking}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">2.4 Parking</div>
    <p>Parking is included with this property.</p>
    {{#if parking_details}}
    <p><strong>Details:</strong> {{parking_details}}</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if has_garden}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">2.5 Garden</div>
    <p>The property includes a garden.</p>
    {{#if garden_maintenance}}
    <p><strong>Maintenance Responsibility:</strong> {{garden_maintenance}}</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- INVENTORY SECTION -->
  {{#if inventory_provided}}
  <div class="inventory-section">
    <div class="inventory-title">üìã Property Inventory</div>
    <div class="important-box">
      <div class="important-title">Inventory Check-In Required</div>
      <p>A comprehensive inventory has been provided. The tenant(s) must check all items within 7 days of moving in and report any discrepancies to the landlord.</p>
    </div>

    {{#if inventory_items}}
    <p><strong>Items Included:</strong></p>
    <div style="white-space: pre-wrap; margin: 15px 0; padding: 15px; background: white; border-left: 3px solid #1e5a8e;">{{inventory_items}}</div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#if white_goods_included}}
    <div class="subsection-title" style="margin-top: 20px;">White Goods & Appliances</div>
    <div class="inventory-grid">
      {{#each white_goods_included}}
      <div class="inventory-item">‚úì {{this}}</div>
      {{/each}}
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="explainer-box" style="margin-top: 20px;">
      <div class="explainer-title">
        <span class="explainer-icon">üí°</span>
        Rights and Responsibilities
      </div>
      <p><strong>Tenant Rights:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use all inventoried items in a reasonable manner</li>
        <li>Report any damage or defects promptly</li>
        <li>Receive replacement of broken items if not due to tenant negligence</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Tenant Responsibilities:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep all items in good condition (fair wear and tear excepted)</li>
        <li>Replace or pay for items damaged due to negligence</li>
        <li>Return all items at end of tenancy</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Right to Change:</strong> The landlord may replace or remove items during the tenancy with reasonable notice, provided equivalent replacements are supplied for essential items.</p>
    </div>

    {{#if professional_cleaning_required}}
    <div class="warning-box" style="margin-top: 15px;">
      <div class="warning-title">Professional Cleaning Required</div>
      <p>The property must be professionally cleaned at the end of the tenancy to the same standard as at the start. Receipts must be provided.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- SECTION 3: TENANCY TERM -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">3</span>
    TENANCY TERM
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">3.1 Start Date & Open-Ended Nature</div>
    <p>This tenancy begins on <strong>{{tenancy_start_date}}</strong>.</p>

    <div class="scotland-legal-box">
      <div class="scotland-legal-title">üè¥Û†ÅßÛ†Å¢Û†Å≥Û†Å£Û†Å¥Û†Åø Scottish PRT - Open-Ended Tenancy</div>
      <p>This is an <strong>open-ended tenancy</strong> with no fixed end date. Under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016, Private Residential Tenancies do not have a fixed term.</p>
      <p><strong>How This Tenancy Can End:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The tenant gives notice (minimum 28 days)</li>
        <li>The landlord applies to the First-tier Tribunal for Scotland with a valid eviction ground</li>
        <li>Both parties agree in writing to end the tenancy</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Important:</strong> The landlord cannot simply end this tenancy - they must have a legal ground and apply to the Tribunal.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 4: RENT -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">4</span>
    RENT
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">4.1 Rent Amount & Payment</div>

    <table class="financial-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Payment Term</th>
          <th>Amount</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="label">Rent Amount</td>
          <td class="value">¬£{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="label">Payment Due</td>
          <td class="value">{{rent_due_day}} of each {{rent_period}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="label">Payment Method</td>
          <td class="value">{{payment_method}}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="subsection-title">4.2 Payment Details</div>
    <div class="party-details">
      <div class="party-label">BANK DETAILS FOR RENT PAYMENTS</div>
      <div class="party-info">
        {{#if bank_account_name}}
        <strong>Account Name:</strong> {{bank_account_name}}<br>
        {{/if}}
        {{#if bank_sort_code}}
        <strong>Sort Code:</strong> {{bank_sort_code}}<br>
        {{/if}}
        {{#if bank_account_number}}
        <strong>Account Number:</strong> {{bank_account_number}}<br>
        {{/if}}
        {{#unless bank_account_name}}
        {{payment_details}}
        {{/unless}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {{#if rent_includes}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">4.3 What Rent Includes</div>
    <p>{{rent_includes}}</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if rent_excludes}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">4.4 What Tenant Pays Separately</div>
    <p>{{rent_excludes}}</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">4.5 Rent Increases</div>
    <div class="scotland-legal-box">
      <div class="scotland-legal-title">Scottish Rent Increase Rules</div>
      <p>Under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016, rent can only be increased if:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>‚úì At least 12 months have passed since the tenancy started or the last rent increase</li>
        <li>‚úì The landlord gives you at least 3 months' notice in writing</li>
        <li>‚úì The increase is fair and reflects market rent</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Tenant Rights:</strong> You can refer the rent increase to a Rent Officer if you believe it is unfair. You must do this within 21 days of receiving the notice.</p>
      {{#if rent_increase_frequency}}
      <p><strong>Agreement:</strong> {{rent_increase_frequency}}</p>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 5: DEPOSIT -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">5</span>
    DEPOSIT
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">5.1 Deposit Amount</div>

    <table class="financial-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Deposit Term</th>
          <th>Amount</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="label">Deposit Amount</td>
          <td class="value">¬£{{deposit_amount}}</td>
        </tr>
        {{#if deposit_scheme_name}}
        <tr>
          <td class="label">Protection Scheme</td>
          <td class="value">{{deposit_scheme_name}}</td>
        </tr>
        {{/if}}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="scotland-legal-box">
      <div class="scotland-legal-title">Scottish Deposit Protection Requirements</div>
      <p><strong>Mandatory Protection:</strong> The landlord MUST protect your deposit in an approved scheme within <strong>30 working days</strong> of receiving it.</p>
      <p><strong>Approved Schemes in Scotland:</strong></p>
      <ul>
